
---	                            
<!-- YAML document start (optional, but good practice) -->
deployment
<!-- Main key recognized by cPanel for deployment actions -->
tasks
<!-- A list of shell tasks to run after Git pull -->
DEPLOYPATH=/home/example/public_html/	
<!-- Defines the path where files will be copied -->
cp index.html $DEPLOYPATH	
<!-- Copies index.html to your live site directory -->
cp style.css $DEPLOYPATH	
<!-- Copies style.css to your live site directory -->

✅ Requirements
1. .cpanel.yml must be in the root of your Git repo.

2. Your repo must be set up via cPanel → Git Version Control.

3. After every push to the repo, cPanel will:
    a. Pull the latest code.
    b. Run the commands in .cpanel.yml.